# Phase 0 — Project Bootstrap

## Motivation

Before building a compiler, we need a proper project.

Equivalent of:

```bash
django-admin startproject
```

for Django.

---

## What We Build

* Project structure
* CLI entrypoint
* Build logs
* Documentation system

---

## Deliverables

```text
apiforge/
├── cli/
├── compiler/
├── docs/
├── tests/
├── examples/
```

Working command:

```bash
apiforge --help
```

---

## Result

You have a real project repository.

---

# Phase 1 — Read API Specification Files

## Motivation

The compiler must understand user input.

Before generating anything we need:

```text
.api file
 ↓
Python object
```

---

## What We Build

Support:

```dsl
resource Product {
    name string
}
```

Simple parsing.

No AST yet.

---

## Deliverables

Command:

```bash
apiforge parse product.api
```

Output:

```json
{
  "resource": "Product",
  "fields": [
    {
      "name": "name",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ]
}
```

---

## Result

APIForge can now read DSL files.

---

# Phase 2 — Generate Django Models

## Motivation

We want the first useful output.

A compiler that generates nothing is useless.

---

## What We Build

Convert:

```dsl
resource Product {
    name string
}
```

into:

```python
class Product(models.Model):
    name = models.CharField(...)
```

---

## Deliverables

Command:

```bash
apiforge generate product.api
```

Output:

```text
generated/
└── models.py
```

---

## Result

You have your first code generation feature.

---

# Phase 3 — Generate CRUD APIs

## Motivation

Models alone aren't useful.

Developers want endpoints.

---

## What We Build

Generate:

```text
models.py
serializers.py
views.py
urls.py
```

---

## Deliverables

Endpoints:

```http
GET /products

POST /products

GET /products/1

PUT /products/1

DELETE /products/1
```

---

## Result

You have a functioning Django REST backend.

This is the first impressive milestone.

---

# Phase 4 — More Field Types

## Motivation

Real APIs need more than strings.

---

## What We Build

Support:

```dsl
string
integer
decimal
boolean
email
```

---

## Deliverables

Example:

```dsl
resource Product {
    name string
    stock integer
    price decimal
}
```

---

## Result

Users can model real business entities.

---

# Phase 5 — Real Compiler Refactor

## Motivation

The parser is becoming messy.

Regexes no longer scale.

Now compiler concepts become necessary.

---

## What We Build

* Lexer
* Tokens
* Parser
* AST

---

## Deliverables

New pipeline:

```text
.api
 ↓
Lexer
 ↓
Tokens
 ↓
Parser
 ↓
AST
```

---

## Result

APIForge becomes a real compiler.

---

# Phase 6 — Semantic Validation

## Motivation

Bad DSL should fail early.

---

## What We Build

Validation:

```dsl
name strng
```

becomes:

```text
Unknown type 'strng'
Did you mean 'string'?
```

---

## Deliverables

Compiler diagnostics.

---

## Result

Compiler catches mistakes.

---

# Phase 7 — Relationships

## Motivation

Real systems are connected.

---

## What We Build

Support:

```dsl
resource Order {
    customer belongs_to Customer
}
```

---

## Deliverables

Generated:

```python
customer = models.ForeignKey(...)
```

---

## Result

Users can build realistic systems.

---

# Phase 8 — Snapshots

## Motivation

We want to remember previous compilations.

Currently compiler forgets everything.

---

## What We Build

Store:

```text
Previous Schema
```

after generation.

---

## Deliverables

```bash
apiforge snapshot
```

---

## Result

Compiler now has memory.

---

# Phase 9 — Diff Engine

## Motivation

This is the project's first truly unique feature.

---

## What We Build

Compare:

```text
Old Schema
```

vs

```text
New Schema
```

---

## Deliverables

Output:

```text
Added field:
Product.stock

Removed field:
Product.price
```

---

## Result

Compiler understands change.

---

# Phase 10 — Migration Planner

## Motivation

Diffs alone are not enough.

Developers need action plans.

---

## What We Build

Convert:

```text
Added field
```

into:

```python
AddField(...)
```

Convert:

```text
Rename field
```

into:

```python
RenameField(...)
```

---

## Deliverables

Migration plans.

---

## Result

Compiler understands evolution.

This is where the project becomes genuinely interesting.

---

# Phase 11 — Watch Mode

## Motivation

Make development feel live.

---

## What We Build

```bash
apiforge watch product.api
```

---

## Deliverables

On save:

```text
Recompiled

Added field:
stock

Migration Plan:
